As a project manager, I evaluate this repository not only from a frontend perspective but also in terms of product readiness, structure, and maintainability. The project demonstrates a solid foundation and already resembles a real-world application rather than a simple student assignment.

## Key Strengths
- Clear product idea and defined domain (clinic system)
- Functional frontend with multiple pages and user flows
- Integration with backend services (API-based interaction)
- Reusable UI components and consistent styling
- Demonstrates real-world development approach (authentication, routing, data flow)

## Key Weaknesses
- Repository structure is not fully standardized
- Lack of documentation for architecture and system design
- Weak commit history quality
- Missing professional-level files (LICENSE, docs, tests)
- Limited clarity in backend/frontend interaction flow

